<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.RendererInterface" Title="RendererInterface package" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    RendererInterface
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>RendererInterface.pkg</TypeRef> header is the platform-neutral entry point for the Cobalt Renderer
      graphics API. It includes the renderer, graphics device, render tree, resource, shader program, helper, token,
      vector, matrix, and shader source information types used to build rendering work.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
      This package deliberately avoids native window system and dynamic library loading bindings. Include
      <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.PlatformBindings">PlatformBindings.pkg</PageRef> as well when an application
      needs SDK helpers for renderer plugin discovery, module lifetime management, SDL3 integration, or native window
      binding structures.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Important">
      <Paragraph>
        Applications that use the C++ SDK normally include this package instead of including individual renderer interface
        headers directly.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[#include <Cobalt/RendererInterface/RendererInterface.pkg>]]></Code>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Types">
    <SubSection Title="Renderer Types">
      <TypeMemberList>
        <TypeMemberListEntry Visibility="Public" Name="IGraphicsDeviceEnumerator" TypeCategory="Interface" PageName="cobalt.graphics.IGraphicsDeviceEnumerator">
          Allows compatible graphics devices to be discovered and retrieved as <TypeRef>IGraphicsDevice</TypeRef> objects
        </TypeMemberListEntry>
        <TypeMemberListEntry Visibility="Public" Name="IGraphicsDevice" TypeCategory="Interface" PageName="cobalt.graphics.IGraphicsDevice">
          Returns specific information on a single graphics device, and allows <TypeRef>IRenderer</TypeRef> instances to be created.
        </TypeMemberListEntry>
        <TypeMemberListEntry Visibility="Public" Name="IRenderer" TypeCategory="Interface" PageName="cobalt.graphics.IRenderer">
          Manages the rendering process, holds the scene tree, and creates all render tree and resource types for the application.
        </TypeMemberListEntry>
      </TypeMemberList>
    </SubSection>
    <SubSection Title="Render Tree Types">
      <TypeMemberList>
        <TypeMemberListEntry Visibility="Public" Name="IRenderPassNode" TypeCategory="Interface" PageName="cobalt.graphics.IRenderPassNode">
          Top level node in the scene tree, binding a frame buffer to the scene.
        </TypeMemberListEntry>
        <TypeMemberListEntry Visibility="Public" Name="IProgramNode" TypeCategory="Interface" PageName="cobalt.graphics.IProgramNode">
          Second level node in the scene tree, binding a shader program to the scene.
        </TypeMemberListEntry>
        <TypeMemberListEntry Visibility="Public" Name="IStateGroupNode" TypeCategory="Interface" PageName="cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode">
          Third level node in the scene tree, binding various state values and resources, and optionally performing compute tasks.
        </TypeMemberListEntry>
        <TypeMemberListEntry Visibility="Public" Name="IRenderableNode" TypeCategory="Interface" PageName="cobalt.graphics.IRenderableNode">
          Fourth level node in the scene tree, defining an object to draw.
        </TypeMemberListEntry>
        <TypeMemberListEntry Visibility="Public" Name="IStateContainer" TypeCategory="Interface" PageName="cobalt.graphics.IStateContainer">
          Base interface for all tree elements that allow bindings and state changes to be applied.
        </TypeMemberListEntry>
        <TypeMemberListEntry Visibility="Public" Name="IDefaultState" TypeCategory="Interface" PageName="cobalt.graphics.IDefaultState">
          Defines a set of attached bindings and state changes, to allow tree node elements to be reused.
        </TypeMemberListEntry>
      </TypeMemberList>
    </SubSection>
